definition: to be irrelevant/to have nothing to do with
appearance/portrait/picture/government minister/(physics) phase/(literary) to appraise (esp. by scrutinizing physical features)/to read sb's fortune (by physiognomy, palmistry etc)
each other/one another/mutually/fret on the neck of a pipa 琵琶[pi2 pa5] (a fret on the soundboard is called a 品[pin3])

sentences.english: Magdalena considered the past an irrelevant encumbrance.
sentences.chinese: 瑪格達萊娜把過去看作毫不相干的累贅。

sentences.english: At first glance, a cold climate did nothing to foster plague.
sentences.chinese: 在一般人印象中，氣候變冷與疾病流行似乎並不相干。

sentences.english: The wind and snow life, all irrelevant.
sentences.chinese: 風與雪花的人生，各不相干。

sentences.english: It was no more of affinity with my real name than black is of kin to white.
sentences.chinese: 這同我的真姓名不相干，正如黑白不同一樣。

sentences.english: These proposals have nothing to do with grandiose schemes for reinventing market capitalism.
sentences.chinese: 這些提議與改造市場資本主義的宏偉計劃毫不相干。

sentences.english: Nor does their education level correlate with their box office earnings.
sentences.chinese: 他們的教育水平也與他們的票房收入不相干。

sentences.english: Some people or other had clothed him in rags out of charity.
sentences.chinese: 一些不相干的人由於行善讓他穿上那樣的破衣爛衫。

sentences.english: There is no chance of any relationship other than one neither wants.
sentences.chinese: 兩不相干是沒有任何機會的。

sentences.english: What does it mean, ideal gas?
Her remarks were beside the question.
sentences.chinese: 她的話與這問題不相干。

sentences.english: Unwittingly, they have been influenced by a completely irrelevant number.
sentences.chinese: 不知不覺，他們已經完全不相干的影響數。

sentences.english: He talked for two hours but his remarks were neither here nor there.
sentences.chinese: 他講了兩個小時，但盡說些不相干的話。

sentences.english: The Karakoram Highway will become irrelevant with the Karakoram highlands going away.
sentences.chinese: 喀喇崑崙高原的喪失使喀喇崑崙公路變得不相干。

sentences.english: I would murder a hundred innocent men if it meant.
sentences.chinese: 只要能夠達到目的，我可以殺一百個不相干的人。

sentences.english: Talking to strangers has nothing to do with tricks or secrets.
sentences.chinese: 和陌生人交談和耍把戲或祕密都毫不相干。

sentences.english: The fact is, these have nothing to do with being poor.
sentences.chinese: 但事實是，這些東西都與他們的貧窮毫不相干。

definition: relevant/to have to do with/coherent (Physics: light etc)
to ask for trouble/to invite difficulties
to have never met sb before (idiom); entirely unacquainted/a complete stranger/not to know sb from Adam
not to get involved/to stay out of it
not to affect sb/irrelevant/of no importance/insignificant
lit. neither a relative nor a friend (idiom)/fig. unrelated to one another in any way
